txt.en: 'Very good, [placeholder]! That ought to keep them away from those folk for a bit!'

Nedda Pinleaf has asked you to seek out Harbingers of the Dead among the more treacherous wilds of Middle-earth.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: Harbingers of the Dead can be found in the following skirmishes: Breaching the Necromancer's Gate, Assault on the Ringwraiths' Lair, The Battle in the Tower, Strike Against Dannenglor, and Protectors of Thangúlhad. You only need to complete four of the five listed quests today to advance this quest.</rgb>

Harbingers of the Dead are assaulting those who dwell in the shadow of Dol Guldur.\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This quest will be removed from your quest log when the event it is associated with ends. </rgb>
Skirmish Assault: Shadows of Dol Guldur
Complete 'Ill Omens: Breaching the Necromancer's Gate'

'[placeholder]!

'I've heard tell that the Harbingers of the Dead have been spotted by the Elves encamped outside Dol Guldur.

'There's no telling what we'll face in that old tower, but I know we can do it!'
Complete 'Ill Omens: Assault on the Ringwraiths' Lair'
Nedda Pinleaf can be found at the skirmish camps of Bree, Ost Galadh, and the Twenty-first Hall.\n\nYou should talk to Nedda Pinleaf.
Complete 'Ill Omens: The Battle in the Tower'
<rgb=#8373ff>A Harbinger of the Dead has appeared!</rgb>
